i Adapting the product  branding to the Japanese consumer

Consumers already liked brands like Dior but theyd never heard of McDonalds so he needed to make it seem like a Japanese brand instead of a US one

Instead of McDonalds he named it Makudonarudo and instead of Ronald McDonald he introduced Donald McDonald

He also changed the menu to better fit the preferences of the Japanese consumer

xB

ii Adapting the GoToMarket to the Japanese consumer

In the US a carfirst country the playbook was to build restaurants outside of cities so customers could come over by car and eat

But Fujita figured people with cars are older Older people dont quickly adjust their eating habits

Who do Young people But young people dont have cars they do have feet though So he decided to build the stores in highdensity cities instead

This is similar to the monumental task of getting asia a tea drinking culture to adopt coffee Which was something Nestle was able to do Wrote about that here Get the younglings to adopt something and eventually youll get the conservative older crowd as well

This is where Fujitas network that hed built over the years with Fujita  Co came in handy His very first location became toptier real estate in Tokyos shopping district

Reminder of Mathematics for Business Professor McCarthys Ps of marketing product  price PLACE  promotion Place is an incredibly important lever

In Europe consumers often assume that if something is German it must be quality engineering Or if its Swiss it must be precise

Fujita was banking on the assumption that if the Japanese consumer would see Americans eating hamburgers in Tokyo theyd desire the product more

This is a beautiful bit of behavioral economics trying to figure out a clever way to make people want what you already have Ie Trying to change consumer preference  demand

Sylvan N Goldman inventor of the shopping cart faced a similar adoption issue Men felt using a shopping cart was too feminine Women felt using a shopping cart was too similar to a baby carriage and turned shopping fun into work not fun He overcame this issue by paying employees to pretend they were shopping consumers That social proof made it acceptable for enough people to try it out and reach critical mass of early adaptors See product adoption curve

One thing that bothered me so much from the start while reading LO was how the relationships between Persephone and her friends were handled I am talking about every single person we are told Perse is friends with  Hades included There are many scenes where she is left alone where ppl that supposedly care about her dont even try to help her and at worst even use her for their benefit

 Here are all Persephones supposed friends

Artemis  probably the biggest dissapointment of them all She is the first character who is shown to have a relationship with Persephone  She is her guide in this world and since Perses arc is all about fitting in and living a new life she shouldve been far more important and present than she actually is Her role as the protector of women is also something that shouldve been a big factor I am not against Artemis having flaws such as her letting men in their apartment when she shouldnt But something had to be done with this flaw of hers Her finding out that Persephone got hurt bcuz of her mistake trying to better herself by being there for Perse all the time wouldve been amazing Instead I cant help but feel that Artemis really doesnt care about others and since she has like no role in this story she has no reason to change Its a shame bcuz this relationship couldve been so meaningful in a story abt women or so it claims to be The myth itself was abt a deep relationship between two women so bringing Artemis herself into the picture was a great opportunity Too bad this is not what we got

Eros I said I can excuse Artemis flaws bcuz they were a great opportunity for character development but here is something I really cant excuse  Why does Eros who knows what happened to Persephone does nothing with that information This character infuriates me so much mostly bcuz I am told to believe that he is a good friend Even Artemis hypocrisy is acknowledged despite the fact that she knows so little so why should I excuse Eros arrogance and ignorance when he is the one that knows the most abt what Perse went thru and the trauma she deals with Perhaps I hate him the most because I had some great hopes with him I never truly liked him but when he finally showed up in season  and the first thing he does is ask abt Persephones sex life I was livid His ignorance and stupidity is baffling to me I dont care that he is a gossiper and is obsessed with all things romance that is actually amazing But if he was supposed to be a comic relief character all this time why make him know the most Now every scene that was supposed to make him lovable will only show how selfish and immature he is Even ignoring the fact that he knows what happened I will have to say that his friendship with Perse is justshallow Thats not a bad thing I believe that his character arc shouldve been focused the most on his relationship with Psyche but the fact that he is considered as Persephones best friend by the fandom and is so praised for no real reason is weird Still I appreciate that he is not friends with Perse for some suspicious reasons unlike other male friends Too bad this doesnt really matter since he is awful for other reasons anyway 

Hermes As much as I love Hermes I dont have a lot of good things to say about him here The most important thing to mention about his friendship with Perse is that he secretly holds romantic feelings for her Bcuz of this most of the things he does are glossed over as something he only did because of those romantic feelings Even more bcuz he also does stuff for money its hard to take their friendship seriously I truly want to believe that he cares for Persephone and that if it wasnt for the possible conflict that would have arised if he got closer he would have had a much bigger role in the story His little crush is not something Im inherently against but I wish there was something more than this and more to their relationship It seems that Perse is only allowed to be best friends with Eros bcuz he certainly cannot have romantic feelings for her and Hermes despite genuinly caring about her is kept at a distance to avoid any possible romantic conflict Despite all this he somehow proved that he was a true friend too bad he wasnt allowed to be there for Persephone

Daphne Im gonna be honest Daphne is a bit of a nothing character We are told that she and Persephone are good friends but there is nothing that indicates that They dont think of eachother at all only when they bump into eachother Moreover Daphne strikes me as extremely egocentric most of the time and her interest in Persephone and Hades relationship only makes her look like a female version of Eros The fact that both Persephone and Daphne had to deal with Apollo was a great opportunity for Persephone to open up as her fear that Daphne mightve become a victim too became another reason to confront this situation But this was just another plot point glossed over Its hard to even care about their relationship when there is so little to it And its a damn shame bcuz Daphne is the closest character we have to Krokos and Withy who also knew Persephone for the longest time Perhaps they were never truly close there is a clear distance between them as Persephone never thought of talking to her about her problemsor maybe she did who knows I just know that the narrative doesnt care abt their friendship

Hera Just like Eros she knows something and does nothing with that information until much much later but unlike with Eros I can atleast somehow understand that maybe she wasnt sure Im sorry for being blunt but she is not Persephones friend thought there was potential There is a clear distance between them and its understandable as to why I think that Hera is too much of a mess to even try to think of a way she couldve been really helpful to Perse and becoming someone she couldve open up to Even tho she does this in the story it all feels forced to resolve a pointless plot point the thing with the sim card This might be only because I dont like Hera but I find her as a pretty bad influence for Persephone So a friendship between them would only work if she tries to better herself too 

Ares  This one is very easy to dismiss This friendship only exists because Ares tried to take advantage of Persephone Unlike with Hermes Ares being kept away from her does not kill the potential for a meaningful friendship bcuz there is not any real potential So I am glad for once Hecate  They sent letters to eachother I dont know what else I think Hecate couldve been a real mentor to Persephone but Im not sure how deep their friendship couldve been as Hecate clearly sees Perse as someone on a different level to her Just like with Hera there is a clear distance between them that its hard to break Demeter  Yes Demeter Bcuz she is also Persephones friend no matter what others would like you to believe Its easy to see from their interactions that they truly care for eachother or at least they did This relationship with all its flaws is the most deepest friendship Persephone ever had Of course the reason why Persephone wanted to leave her mother was to form other friendships Which is how to form other more healthy relationships Codependent habits can evolve in those who suffered neglect in childhood and did not have their needs met in this formative period This mistreatment lends itself to low selfworth fear of abandonment and difficulty asserting emotional needs Codependecy is a need to be needed as though life has no meaning without it and althought we do not get enough of Demeter its easy to assume that this is what she is going thru Demeter is functional person nonetheless and was able to recognize her daughters needs and let her go despite the risks I think this alone proves how deeply Demeter cares for Persephone more than any other character She fought her own fears for her And now is this all her efforts have amounted to  seeing Hades who was against her and even insulted her become the most important person in Persephones life No wonder she wants to make everything as it once was I could talk about Demeter for hours but what I want to make clear is that Demeter is not a bad person shes a deeply hurt personwho now faces the prospect of the most important relationship in her life crumbling So its a shame seeing how this relationship and Demeters character in general has been so neglected Their relationship had the potential to be the most meaningful in the whole story but instead felt like an afterthoughtAnd now Hades  Persephones relationship with Hades is described as above all else romantic  But for a romance to be truly meaningful and impactful we ironically need more than romance Its hard to find out which actions of his where done out of care for Persephone as a friend when everything is glossed over as romantic Despite this Hades is clearly the closest person to Perse and thus her biggest friend so its very important to take it into consideration I said before this that I had problems with Eros arrogance Daphne being egocentric Hera being a mess and a bad influence and Demeter being codependent Well guess what Hades has all of that I get a headache everytime I think of him and his intentions as I have to break the biggest walls of romance fluffiness Ive ever seen That said their relationship is very similar Demeters relationship with Persephone when it comes to codependency except this relationship is marked time and time again as being better I believe this is a detriment to Hades and Persephones characters Hades in particular has a lot of issues that he never truly healed so its more than hypocritical to condemn Demeter for having similar issues while ignoring Hades and even praising him He also doesnt encourage growth in Persephone and even shelters her from questioning herself He is also sheltered by the narrative to never better himself 

This being the most important and the only deep relationship in Persephones life actively ruins her story her chances to grow as a characterIt feels cruel to see her relationship with her mother being deemed as meaningless when there was so much to learn from it And its such a shame seeing every other relationship being so halfbaked and disregarded for the sake of paying more attention on romance and a relationship that is just stagt and downright unsatisfying to read about

So what do you all think about Persephones friends Do you think that these relationships help her to heal and better herself in any way  Does Persephone have any real friends

UHS group counseling sessions are free for all UC Berkeley students and do not require health insurance

Mondays

 Graduate Mens Support  Mondays    pm Feb   May  Virtual  Facilitated by Richard Chiovarelli PsyD  Description This weekly support group is offered for students who selfidentify as male grad students who wish to come together to discuss the challenges of being a grad student ways to deal with the hurdles  hassles of school find ways to connect with others discuss relationship issues and consider ways to manage stress  live a balanced life as a Berkeley student 
 Starting a New Medication for Anxiety or Depression  Monthly Every First Monday  pm Jan   May  Virtual  Facilitated by Raghav Suri PsyD  Description This singlesession psychoeducational group covers the basic facts of common anxiety and depression medications and factors that increase the likelihood of effectiveness The group discusses tips and tricks for effective communication with your prescriber for ongoing medication management
 Worry Stress and Your Health  Monthly Every Second Monday    pm Jan   May  Virtual  Facilitated by Raghav Suri PsyD  Description This singlesession group is focused on increasing your understanding of  the bodys physical sensations and responses  the different ways that persistent worry about our health may impact our stress response and behaviors and  strategies for coping with thoughts behaviors and emotions related to health pain and physiological sensations
 Holistic Sleep Wellness Behavioral Changes to Reduce Insomnia and Sleep Difficulties  Monthly Every Third Monday    pm Jan   May  Virtual  Facilitated by Raghav Suri PsyD  Description This singlesession psychoeducational group is based on the concept of holistic sleep wellness It focuses on increasing your understanding of the mechanisms and habits that impact your sleep in order to help you identify and experiment with behaviors that can improve your sleep and work for you your body and your life
 Graduate Womens Support  Mondays    pm Jan   May  Virtual  Facilitated by Linda Zaruba PhD  Description This support group is offered for students who selfidentify as female graduate students who wish to come together to share the challenges and struggles of being a grad student discuss ways to balance school  personal life discuss relationships with advisors and peers increase selfconfidence and develop relationships with other women in grad school

Tuesdays

 Survivor Support Group  Tuesdays    pm Feb   Apr  Virtual  Facilitated by Tiffany Lin LCSW and KG Gerich MSW  Description This group provides a supportive environment for survivors of sexual assault to gather together and build community Participants will learn to better understand their present lives in the context of their experiences while learning and practicing skills in grounding and mindfulness Join this support group of survivors to reclaim a sense of personal power and wellbeing as we know healing is amplified by connection This group is open to survivors of all genders This group requires a pregroup meeting with the group facilitator before joining Please call Social Services at   to set up an intake with the group facilitator to get started
 Alcohol and Other Drug  Harm Reduction Group  Tuesdays    pm Virtual Facilitated by Justin Castello PhD  Description This weekly group acknowledges that different goals work for different people With the support of the group you can work on finding the right balance for yourself in order to get what you want from your substance use choices without the things you dont want Please call Social Services at   to set up an intake with the group facilitator to get started
 BIMOC Black Indigenous Men of Color Healing Circle  Tuesdays    pm Feb   May  Virtual  Facilitated by Adisa Anderson PhD  Description This healing circle is offered for selfidentified Black Indigenous and Men of Color who want to build community through shared solidarity discuss ways to be rooted in resilience and explore ways to be centered in mind body and spirit We discuss the complexities of navigating life at UC Berkeley including our intersecting identities microaggressions and isms academics career family relationships and maintaining holistic wellbeing This group requires a brief pregroup meeting with the group facilitators before joining
 Black Womxns Sister Circle  Tuesdays    pm Anna Head    Facilitated by Jaiza Jones LCSW  Description The weekly group is designed to provide a supportive space for undergraduate and graduate selfidentified Black Womxn to explore the challenges of navigating life at UC Berkeley It provides a weekly opportunity to engage in cultivating selfcare and wellness practices to build meaningful connections and create a mutually supportive and inclusive community All Black students who experience life through the lens of womxn in body spirit identitypast present future and fluid GenEq are welcome 
 Healing Through Grief and Loss  Tuesdays    pm Feb   May  Anna Head    
Facilitated by cy TavolacciArista LCSW  Description In this week process group we will explore some of the teachings of grief share how we maintain a relational connection to our ancestors and loved ones beyond death and support one another in coping with the strong emotions that accompany us on our healing journey This is for UC Berkeley students only who have experienced a loss  months ago or more For more recent losses please call   and make an appointment with a counselor for individual support To sign up for this group please call   and speak with a counselor directly cy will reach out to you directly for a brief pregroup meeting 
 Mindfulness Meditation DropIn Group  Tuesday    pm Feb   Apr  Virtual  Facilitated by KinMing Chan PhD  Description Meditation has a lot of health benefits such as reducing stress improving relaxation enhancing sense of wellbeing and alleviating health symptoms This dropin group is set up for students who want to try meditation and explore some techniques to do it There is no need for commitment to come to all sessions  Students who have experience doing meditation are also welcome to join to meditate together as well
 LGBTQIA Support Group  Tuesday    pm Feb   May  Virtual  Facilitated Denise Goitia LCSW and Kehan Shen MS  Description This is a virtual group for students who identify as LGBTQIA as well as those who are questioning and exploring Join us in cocreating a supportive and affirming space to explore themes that promote wellness and connection Topics will include but are not limited to coming out identity development family of origin chosen family relationships dating healthcare intersectional and multicultural identities living out on campus building communities of support nonmonogamy and stress management This group requires a brief pregroup meeting with a group facilitator before joining We accept new group members on an ongoing basis and students may join after the start date If interested email  or call us at  

Wednesdays

 Wellness in Action DropIn  Wednesdays    pm Mar    Mar  Virtual  Facilitated by Tegan Adams PsyD and Brad Cameron  Description These week skillbuilding groups are for students experiencing stress mild to moderate anxiety panic and depression Participants will learn mental health and general wellness strategies to build personal awareness develop coping strategies and integrate wellness techniques into their daily routines Participants will have an opportunity to engage in discussion as well as to give and receive support Topics include selfcare eg sleep exercise nutrition thinking patterns and mood mindfulness resilience and fostering positive connections
 Understanding Self  Others  Wednesdays    pm Mar   May  Virtual  Facilitated by Tegan Adam PsyD and Sheela Vashishtha LCSW  Description This week therapy group is designed to foster greater selfawareness and more satisfying relationships by exploring how your background and upbringing affect your relationships becoming more aware of your thoughts and feelings and exploring your hereandnow feelings with other group members  This group requires a brief pregroup meeting with the group facilitators before joining
 Asian  Asian American Womxn Support Group  Wednesdays    pm Feb   Apr  Virtual  Facilitated by Angelica Yi MSW  Description This group is for students who identify as womxn of any Asian or AsianAmerican background Well cocreate a supportive space to share experiences related to intersectional identities navigating Asian  American values racismrelated trauma school stress family  relationship issues and other topics of interest This group requires a brief pregroup meeting with the group facilitators before joining All Asian and Asian American students who experience life through the lens of womxn in body spirit identitypast present future and fluid are welcome GenEq including those who identify as woman womxn femme nonbinary gender nonconforming etc
 Heartspeak Undocumented Student Program USP Support Group  Wednesday    pm Feb   May  Chavez   Facilitated by Diana Peña PhD  Description This weekly support space for undocumented students at Cal will center social connection as a foundation for wellness racialtrauma healing and resilience  This group requires a brief pregroup meeting with the group facilitators before joining  You may directly schedule your prescreen appointment online via wejoinincomUSPmentalhealth

Thursdays

 Gender Support Group  Thursday    pm Feb   May  Virtual  Facilitated by Hez Wollin LCSW and Mar Chung PhD  Description This group is for transgender nonbinary gender expansive agender gender diverse genderqueer gender nonconforming students to come together in a safe collaborative nonjudgemental space Together we will discuss a variety of topics related to being on the gender spectrum including gender identity intersectional identities different aspects of transition coming out and being out at UC Berkeley navigating family of origin considerations community resources academic stress relationships sexuality and resilience and joy  The group requires a pregroup meeting with facilitators before joining 
 Pathways to Health and Healing  Thursday    pm Feb   Mar  Virtual Facilitated by Erin OConnor LCSW and Shanta Jambotkar LCSW  Description This virtual weekly group will take place across five sessions and is intended for UC Berkeley students who navigate the impacts of physical injuries andor newly diagnosed or chronic health conditions Welcoming of all social and cultural identities the space aims to build a studentcentered community for coping and thriving Themes may include mindbody stress management chronic illness and relationships health and identity and navigating systems healthcare DSP Members will have an opportunity to reflect on lived experiences and exchange and cocreate strategies that promote healing in their daily lives If interested please contact Social Services at   to connect with a group facilitator
 Building Healthy Relationships  Thursday    pm Mar    Apr   Tang Center  Facilitated by Emily ElOqlah PhD and Karen Lee Tsugawa LMFT  Description This week group is designed to help students build skills to develop healthy relationships with others from potential romantic partners to platonic relationships with friends Topics include recognizing our relational patterns values boundaries and communication styles We will also discuss how our cultural and familial backgrounds influence our relationships with others The group is open to undergraduates and graduates To sign up for this group please call   speak with a counselor directly or register yourself at bitlyuhsgroups Emily or Karen will reach out to you directly for a brief pregroup meeting
 Asian American Community Voice  Thursdays    pm BiWeekly Sep   Dec    César Chavez Student Center  Facilitated by Junichi Shiamoka PsyD andor Jeff Lee LCSW  Description We are a support and conversation space for AsianAsian American South Asian Southeast Asian Pilipinx East Asian and multiracialethnic students  Its a dropin informal support space where we discuss topics relevant to our communities including but not limited to taking care of ourselves and our community exploring intersecting identities navigating stressors like family expectations xenophobia and racial injustice and celebrating the diversity among Asian communities and more Come for the topics you are interested in or join regularly for our conversation Find the calendar of suggested topics here bitlyRkqXX

 From SelfCriticism to Kindness  Friday    am Feb   Mar  Virtual  Facilitated by Amy Honigman PhD  Description This group will provide a space for students to learn skills for building selfcompassion and kindness as well as opportunities to offer support to one another Topics will include fostering an attitude of kindness towards self  others building selfesteem through selfacceptance and using mindfulnessmediation to facilitate resilience motivation  selfconfidence
 Alcohol and Other Drug  Harm Reduction Group  Friday    pm  Facilitated by Robin Walley LCSW and Jennifer Tai MSW  Description This weekly group acknowledges that different goals work for different people With the support of the group you can work on finding the right balance for yourself in order to get what you want from your substance use choices without the things you dont want Please call Social Services at   to set up an intake with the group facilitator to get started Spring  Group Counseling Schedule

Wanted to give some info as I see a lot of different info on this forum in regards to buying a new bracelet from an AD whether its buying a jubilee or an oyster for your GMT

A few months ago after about a year was happy to get call from AD offering me a BLRO on an oyster Obviously I bought it Dont get me wrong I think it looks great on an oyster as well but on this model I was really wanting it on a jubilee 

About a month after purchase I asked if I could order a jubilee for my GMT he said no problem it was  and he told he me he couldnt give me a time frame could be a couple weeks to a couple of months Fast forward  weeks it came in and he put the jubilee on it for me and I love it

During this time I spoke to AD not sales person and asked a few questions based on things I read here andor Rolex forums

They do NOT take your original bracelet back nor are you required to trade it in

 You do NOT need to put the original bracelet back on to get it serviced As long as the model in question is offered with both bracelets they are interchangeable and do not effect warranty

I personally am keeping original oyster bracelet because I think its cool to be able to swap but once again its your bracelet you can do what you want with it

Hope this helps GMT Jubilee bracelet AD came through

In case you are curious I would recommend reading the practice of brahmacharya by Swami Sivada In yoga alchemy was never coded The divine marriage of Shiva and Shakti as a result of an oordhvareta yogi oordhvareta refers to an upstream of sexual energy instead of its downflow due to the corruptionabuse of shakti via lust forcing shakti to be expelled into maya encapsulates the whole process similar to the baphomet and hermesAsclepius symbols This requires absolute chastity and not having any leaks of ojas which obviously refers to its crude form as semen but also to the leakage of the subtleethereal prima materia ie ojas the divine creative force ie the ether the only know substance that is both spiritual as well as material Ojas when further refined leads to the opening of sahasrara the crown chakra Main symptoms that show that you are doing it right is when your eyes and face start shiningglowing slightly and your limbal rings grow back These are the results of transmuted ojas also called tejas which means shine iirc Eyes are the window of the soul as a proverb as well as the hagiographies of halos Both of these are results that necessitate purity as well as an accumulation of ojas

The overall impressions of highend fashion brands and their perceived quality or value are

 Some Redditors on rfemalefashionadvice commented that certain highend brands come across as cheap or unflattering to them
     
     The first one that comes to mind is MZ Wallace To me they look like a cross between quilted bags that were popular  years ago and puffer jackets
     Ill also admit that I didnt realize that Missoni was a luxury brand for way too long To me their busy stripes on knits tend to look very unflattering
 Others on rfemalefashionadvice advised that its perfectly fine to pair a designer bag with more casual shoes as long as your overall look is cohesive

Her behavior behind my back to her son my husband

 She gives unsolicited advice eg she needs therapy to be in touch with her dreams like me
 She gifts backhanded compliments eg wow shes so smart but then again probably too smart
 She denigrates our relationship eg you dont seem happy with her you dont seem yourself
 She compares me to other people she dislikes eg shes just like your uncles narcissistic exwife
 She rants about our lack of children eg you always wanted lots of kids before you met her

 She sends accidental texts about me eg oops I meant to send that text to your sisteraunt
 She puts me down in relation to her eg Im a magimous person she should learn from me

Difference between drugstore midrange and high end

 Drugstore Massdrugstore brands usually are released with wide distribution at accessible price points and designed for a large audience
 Midrange Straddle the line between drugstore and high end
 Highend Niche unapologetically expensive and have more limited distributionretail presence than mass brands Also associated with high end fashion brands

I just want to gush about this episode for a minute I hope thats okay

First of all I love that this episode is the plot of Miss Congeniality I know Ellen DeGeneres likes to claim its because Marc Lawrence watched her training to walk in a dress and high heels butCmon Its basically the same plot Also on my second watch I caught the joke about Gabby having clams for dinner that I missed the first time 

I dont particularly care for Salmoneus Hes probably my least favorite recurring character in the early seasons Despite his presence I think this is one of my top ten episodes of the show and that is solely for one reason 

Miss Artiphys played by Karen Dior whose name appears before Robert Trebors in the opening credits

In fact its Miss Artiphys that is the reason I went back and rewatched this episode tonight As I was watching the series its the one episode I kept going back to in my mind I really cant believe it aired in  honestly

Im not a trans woman Im a trans man but I am trans and this episode I wasnt expecting anything like it when I started the show and it blew my mind the first time I saw it Blew my mind again tonight

When Miss Artiphys appeared I remember the first time I was watching it made my stomach drop Oh no I thought Are they going to make the trans woman the villain The way they had Xena look at her the music that played that moment of tension I recognized it and not in a good way 

There are parts of this episode that arent great Xena ripping off Miss Artiphyss wig makes me cringe just as much the second time watching it But the conversation that follows that

I was just trying to scare you  
  
Whyd you wanna scare me  
  
Because I knew you knew You know about me And I didnt want you telling anyone  
  
What made you think Id tell 

This This was the moment I started to relax a little

You really dont get it do you I guess being born a woman you wouldnt This is a chance to use a part of me most people usually laugh at or worse A part I usually have to hide Only here that part works for me you see  
  
I think so   
  
Look I dont expect you to understand And Im sorry I got you steamed I just hope you let me quit the pageant in private instead of going public with it  
  
No way May the best person win

Ill admit The first time I watched this scene I got a little teary In a perfect world Xena would have said May the best woman win but for  Not only did they include a conversation that removed the trans character as the potential villian but had Xena sympathizing with her The script is empathetic towards her character in a way that I was not expecting Thank you Chris Manheim

And then Miss Artiphys places as a top five semifinalist I was already loving the episode for turning my expectations on their head in the nicest way possible so when that happened I was honestly a little surprised I figured her saving Xenas butt would be the end of her role in the episode honestly 

Yes for Miss Artiphyss talent skit shes ribbon dancing to circus music I dont love it But I think the ending makes up for it Because the ending man The ending is what really got me about this episode Because I know Miss Artiphys was technically the fifth runner upbut the show also made a point of giving her a scene where she talks about how important the pageant is to her Unlike the other contestants she doesnt think its a crock Miss Artiphys wants to be there Its the first time in her life shes been able to really be herself And Xena knows that She gets it 

When she steps down she inspires the rest of the contestants who arent in it for themselves to step down too Oh sure technically you could argue that they dont know Xena was Miss Amphipolis but Salmoneous isnt exactly subtle and she doesnt look that different in a blonde wig 

So Xena steps down and the other three step down and Miss Artiphys gets to be Miss Known World

A trans woman is Miss Known World 

The joy she feels is palatable Hearing Salmoneous sing about her and describe her as the perfect woman makes my joy palatable And I love the way she pulls Xena in for a kiss

The ending dialogue between Xena and Gabrielle could have been better Calling her a man was Not my favorite moment To me Miss Artiphys is clearly meant to be a trans woman not least because shes played by one 

But then But then

Gabrielle asks Its kinda funny huh

And Xena asks why

Why 

Why is it funny What was the joke Miss Artiphys clearly felt like she was a woman She was happy as a woman Except for Xena and Gabrielle and Salmoneous at the end no one knows she wasnt born a woman Shes Miss Known World

Beauty is beauty Xena says

And peace is peace Gabrielle replies

Sure the last bit of dialogue is drag jokes from Gabrielle but that doesnt really matter Not when Miss Artiphys ends the episode as Miss Known World And not when Xena shuts her down Pretty firmly 

 I just cant believe it  I cant believe they wrote an episode that included a trans woman That gave the trans woman a role That let her save the day for Xena That was empathetic 

That let her win

Thank you Xena Here She Comes Miss Amphipolis

Hello

I am D a sociology student from Brazil I am also a poet as many people in my family and procrastinator I am easily fascinated by everything I have been fascinated by half of the countries on Earth many political figures Lin Biao De Gaulle Nixon and so on Besides poetry I love reading though I dont do as often as Id like because of university cinema politics history architecture and urbanism though I dont know much about it photography and so on I have two dogs and I would be glad to send pictures of them I am learning French and I will probably go study French in Montreal next year I also plan to continue my studies either there or in Portugal France or Belgium I have very poor German too and some notions of Russian

My favourite books are AutodaFé by Elias Canetti Anna Karienina by Tolstoy The Sound and the Fury by Faulkner Journey to the End of the Night by Céline and Vast Emotions and Imperfect Thoughts by Rubem Fonseca My favourite poets are Pessoa and T S Eliot My favourite movies are La Chinoise Manila in the Claws of the Light High and Low Straw Dog Chinatown Metropolitan and Taste of Cherry My favourite musicians are Piazzolla Milton Nascimento Spinetta Chico Buarque Bartók Kendrick Lamar and Stromae but ultimately I have been in love with Ariana Grande Françoise Hardy Jane Birkin Aznavour Gainsbourg C Tangana Rosalía and  Savage 

I am somewhat leftleaning I believe in the welfare state and I think the state should help the poorest and tax the rich for that I believe in free trade and market economy but I also believe the state should intervene in the economy when necessary I am for the legalization of abortion marijuana and euthanasia and decriminalization of all drugs Expansion of certain public services and agrarian and urban reform Affirmative action for minority groups Black and Indigenous peoples LGBTQIA et cetera Protection of the environment and carbon tax I truly believe in a laic state and I think religion should stay away from government If you are Brazilian or into Brazilian politics I voted for Marina and Haddad in  and for Lula in both rounds this year Yes I was very happy and relieved when he won 

I suffer with Bipolar Disorder as my grandmother did and my father probably does That means I am very often depressed and in fact I am going to try a new treatment because of it Spravato I might become a bit withdrawn or euphoric because of it but it is usually harmless for people other than me 

Some curiosities about me

 I have an inherited coat of arms registered in the institution responsible for it and I am pretty interested in genealogy There is a biography of my th greatgrandfather written after a historian called him an opportunist I have read twice

 I have sat in a place where politicians of a certain party rest in the National Congress while politicians probably made some shady deals the party is notoriously corrupt and drank Coke

 I love Hermès ties and I just dont buy them because Id never wear them I know the location of Hermès stories throughout the World

 I appeared on TV once but never got famous 

 I have a collection of editions of Du Monde Entier Gallimard because of a hypomanic episode 

 I have a speech problem and often succeeded in making people believe I was a foreigner when I was a child and teen

 I have thought about writing a novel either about my life but fictionalized of course a VW Beetle or about Kissinger

 I emailed twice Noam Chomsky and he replied twice

Three nice songs to thank you for reading this







Anyways I hope you will reach out to me M Brazil  bored sociology student poet kind of a journalist and vagabond looks for people

 Overwatch  Retail Patch Notes  January  

A new patch is now live on PC Xbox PlayStation and Nintendo Switch Read below to learn more about the latest changes

To share your feedback please post in the General Discussion   
For a list of known issues visit the Bug Report   
For troubleshooting assistance visit the Technical Support  forum

 HERO UPDATES

 Tank

Orisa

Fortify

 Health bonus reduced from  to 

Roadhog

Chain Hook

 Impact damage reduced from  to 
 The enemy final position distance from Roadhog after being pulled increased from  to  meters

Scrap Gun

 Damage per pellet reduced from  to 
 Recovery time reduced from  to  seconds
 Reload time reduced from  to  seconds
 Maximum ammo increased from  to 

Developer comments These changes aim to reduce the frustration of dying in one shot immediately after being hooked and pulled by Roadhog Chain Hook is still a powerful utility to forcibly reposition enemy players so it will still often lead to eliminations Its effectiveness will now be more dependent on specific hero matchups and how the hooked target is able to respond

 Damage

Sojourn

Railgun

 Energy gain is no longer based on damage done by primary fire Each primary fire hit against an enemy player now grants  energy
 Primary fire damage per projectile reduced from  to 

Developer comments The energy gain adjustment will help smooth out Sojourns average Railgun charge time because it wont benefit as much from critical damage or damage boost abilities Hitting armored targets or other sources of damage reduction will result in quicker energy gains than before

Previously damage boosts and critical damage had an amplified effect for Sojourn since it reduced the time to build energy and lowered the threshold at which her Railgun secondary fire became lethal The reduction to primary fire damage will further slow that down as well

 Support

Kiriko

Healing Ofuda

 Recovery time increased from  to  second

Developer comments Despite Kirikos healing projectiles being slowmoving and single target her average healing output per match is higher than wed like Weve seen players tend to get overly focused on maximizing her healing potential and only use primary fire for extended periods of time Rather than reduce the amount of healing per projectile which may lead to feeling locked into focusing on primary fire even more were increasing the recovery time before she can start firing the Healing Ofuda Increasing recovery times opens the opportunity to weave in secondary fire Kunai more freely

 BUG FIXES

 GENERAL

 Adjusted footstep audio mixing to make enemy footsteps more audible

 HEROES

Lucio

 Fixed an issue with Lucios Hermes skin exhibiting incorrect physics

Reinhardt

 Fixed an issue with Reinhardts Hammer appearing deformed during the Sweethardt emote

Sojourn

 Fixed an issue where Sojourns Cyber Detective Skin would fail to load

Wrecking Ball

 Fixed an issue with Adaptive Shield where it could be incorrectly applied before the cooldown was complete OVERWATCH  RETAIL PATCH NOTES   JAN

Good Friday morning traders and investors of the rStockMarketChat sub Welcome to the final trading day of this week Here are your premarket movers  news this AM



CLICK HERE TO VIEW THE FULL SOURCE

Stock futures rise after Dow goes negative for the year


 Stock futures were higher on Friday as investors tried to hang onto the January rally amid worries about monetary policy and slowing earnings

 Futures tied to the Dow Jones Industrial Average dipped  points or less than  SP  and Nasdaq futures gained  and  respectively

 Google rose  after the company announced it will lay off  employees Netflix jumped  after posting more subscribers than expected even though its quarterly earnings missed analysts estimates

 Wall Street is coming off another down session with the Dow and the SP  posting threeday losing streaks as corporate earnings and economic data signal a slowing economy The Dow slipped more than  points or  and is now down  year to date The SP  shed  and the Nasdaq Composite lost  but both indexes are positive for the year

 For the week all three indexes are on track to close lower The Dow is down  on track for its worst week since September The SP  is down more than  and could notch its worst weekly performance since December The Nasdaq is down more than  and on pace to break a twoweek win streak

 The market is focused and is not sure how to react between the backward looking Fed analysis of the market versus the forward and leading indicators of the market said Tim Seymour founder and chief investment officer of Seymour Asset Management on CNBCs Fast Money

 Those forward indicators include economic data such as retail sales and industrial production This is where the market is starting to break down he said

 Going forward investors will continue to watch corporate earnings with oilfield services name SLB and Ally Ficial set to report Friday They will also listen closely to speeches from Fed officials ahead of the central banks February meeting seeking clues on the size of the rate hike thats likely forthcoming

I tie a plastic ice pack around my face and commence with the mornings stretching exercises

Afterwards I stand in front of a chrome and acrylic Washmobile bathroom sink  with soap dish cup holder and railings that serve as towel bars which I bought at Hastings Tile to use while the marble sinks I ordered from Finland are being sanded  and stare at my reflection with the ice pack still on

I pour some Plax antiplaque formula into a stainlesssteel tumbler and swish it around my mouth for thirty seconds

Then I squeeze Rembrandt onto a faux tortoiseshell toothbrush and start brushing my teeth too hung over to floss properly  but maybe I flossed before bed last night and rinse with Listerine

Then I inspect my hands and use a nailbrush

I take the icepack mask off and use a deeppore cleanser lotion

Then an herbmint facial masque which I leave on for ten minutes while I check my toenails

Then I use the Probright tooth polisher and next the Interplak tooth polisher this in addition to the toothbrush which has a speed of  rpm and reverses direction fortysix times per second the larger tufts clean between teeth and massage the gums while the short ones scrub the tooth surfaces

I rinse again with Cepacol I wash the facial massage off with a spearmint face scrub

In the shower I use first a wateractivated gel cleanser then a honeyalmond body scrub and on the face an exfoliating gel scrub

Vidal Sassoon shampoo is especially good at getting rid of the coating of dried perspiration salts oils airborne pollutants and dirt that can weigh down hair and flatten it to the scalp which can make you look olderThe conditioner is also good  silicone technology permits conditioning benefits without weighing down the hair which can also make you look older

On weekends or before a date I prefer to use the Greune Natural Revitalizing Shampoo the conditioner and the Nutrient Complex These are formulas that contain Dpanthenol a vitaminBcomplex factor polysorbate  a cleansing agent for the scalp and natural herbs

Over the weekend I plan to go to Bloomingdales or Bergdorfs and on Evelyns advice pick up a Foltene European Supplement and Shampoo for thinning hair which contains complex carbohydrates that penetrate the hair shafts for improved strength and shine Also the Vivagen Hair Enrichment Treatment a new Redken product that prevents mineral deposits and prolongs the life cycle of hair Luis Carruthers recommended the Aramis Nutriplexx system a nutrient complex that helps increase circulation

Once out of the shower and toweled dry I put the Ralph Lauren boxers back on and before applying the Mousse A Raiser a shaving cream by Pour Hommes I press a hot towel against my face for two minutes to soften abrasive beard hair

Then I always slather on a moisturizer to my taste Clinique and let it soak in for a minute You can rinse it off or keep it on and apply a shaving cream over it  preferably with a brush which softens the beard as it lifts the whiskers  which Ive found makes removing the hair easierLeave the sideburns and chin for last since these whiskers are tougher and need more time to soften Rinse the razor and shake off any excess water before starting

Afterwards splash cool water on the face to remove any trace of lather You should use an aftershave lotion with little or no alcohol Never use cologne on your face since the high alcohol content dries your face out and makes you look older One should use an alcoholfree antibacterial toner with a watermoistened cotton ball to normalize the skin

Applying a moisturizer is the final step Splash on water before applying an emollient lotion to soften the skin and seal in the moisture

Next apply Gel Appaisant also made by Pour Hommes which is an excellent soothing skin lotion If the face seems dry and flaky  which makes it look dull and older  use a clarifying lotion that removes flakes and uncovers fine skin it can also make your tan look darker

Then apply an antiaging eye balm Baume Des Yeux followed by a final moisturizing protective lotion

A scalpprogramming lotion is used after I towel my hair dry I also lightly blowdry the hair to give it body and control but without stickiness and then add more of the lotion shaping it with a Kent natural bristle brush and finally slick it back with a widetooth comb American Psycho Book Skin Care

NXT is the developmental system for the future superstars of WWE with notable talents such as Kevin Owens Sami Zayn Becky Lynch and numerous others who have gone on to do something great for the land of sports entertainment On September th  the brand entered a rebirth including new talents such and now with those acts possibly moving on to greater and grander on the main roster leaving everyone with the question is whos NXT next crop of talent to ascend WWE to newer heights 

Heres how Id book NXT after WrestleMania  

Alexa play  Apollo Kids

NXT

Its the NXT after WrestleMania weekend and we open the show with the celebration of the NEW NXT Champion Grayson Waller He talks about he left Stand and Deliver victorious and getting of rid of the meatheaded gremlin Bron Breakker and the dripless Carmelo Hayes concluding that were living in the Grayson Waller era and whoever thinks that they can take the title of his hands can step but be prepared to be disappointed

The main event announced for tonight is the new North American Champion Tony DAngelo defending the title in a rematch from Stand and Deliver against former champion Wes Lee Throughout the night its announced that the mens Breakout Tournament will return and feature talents like Oba Femi Lucien Price Karl Fredericks and Dragon Lee to compete

NXT also has a new Womens Champion and her name is Tiffany Stratton she brags about capitalizing a wounded Roxanne Perez wanting these losers in the audience to realize that her reign was nothing but a fairytale and that Perez will never hold this again A wounded Perez comes out and reminds her that she still has a rematch clause but lets her know not to get too comfortable because she will regain her title

Other things that have happened in NXT Briggs and Jensen have broken up with Jensen aligning with Kiana James Upsetting Briggs and Fallon Henley the two teams competed in mixed tag team action at Stand and Deliver with James revealing that she now owns Henleys family bar Gallus continuing their rampage on the tag team division since their victory at Vengeance Day and submitting their legacy with a victory over The Good Brothers at Stand and Deliver

The Creed Brothers have been defeated by Jinder and Co with Sanga finally embracing his inner beast and putting Brutus Creed on the shelf leaving Julius to tear them apart by himself The Schism continue torturing Axiom Carter and Chance still dominated the tag team division and the womens division still on lock with Isla Dawn Blair Davenport Nikkita Lyons Sol Ruca etc

Tony DAngelo w Stacks v Wes Lee Singles match for the NXT North American Championship

Lee and DAngelo starts off the match with a lockup but the former champion uses his agility against the champions rugged style After the challenger attempted an aerial attack the champion counters with a strike and begins to dominate targeting his challengers wounded right leg 

After applying a figure four leglock on the challenger the champion continues to dominate until his opponent fights out of it and gains some momentum capitalizing it with an jumping clothesline Lee begins to deliver some more moves and was going for a corner attack but was distracted by Stacks that gave the champion the opportunity to take advantage and deliver his signature Fisherman Buster to retain the title 

Tony DAngelo retains via pinfall

After DAngelo celebrates Grayson Waller rushes back into the ring and states he should open and close show and before he could continue he was interrupted by a returning Tyler Bate and the champion tries to attack him but is put on his ass with Bate declaring himself as the next challenger

On the following NXT Waller looks to redeem himself and refuses for Bate to have any advantage in their upcoming title match but the challenger just continues to have one up against the champion We also get an introduction to the competitors in the Breakout Tournament Briggs and Henley enters her old family bar and disgusted with the changes but are eventually thrown out teasing another match between the two couples And DAngelo gets a little arrogant and decides to give the winner of the tournament a shot at his North American Championship At the end of the night Bate is victorious against Xyon Quinn and before celebrating hes attacked by Waller finally get one over against his challenger

NXT

Karl Fredericks v Oba Femi

Fredericks uses the official as a shield to prevent from being in Femis clutches and tries to have an advantage in the match he nails his opponent with a cheap tactic and begins to dominate the match against his opponent After stomping on his opponents right leg and nailing some strikes to his opponent but Oba fights back and gains some minor momentum and tried to deliver a powerhouse move but his right leg gave out That gave Fredericks the advantage to continue the assault on his right leg and delivered a heel hook to get the submission victory 

Karl Fredericks wins via submission 

Dragon Lee v Lucien Price

Before the opening bell Price attacks Lee from behind showcasing that he is the next No One Contender for the North American Championship He continues the assault against the former IWGP Junior champion and attempted an outside attack but was countered by his opponent 

Lee gains some momentum and delivered his strikes and agilities and he tried to deliver a springboard assault but his opponent dodges Price attempts to deliver a superplex but Lee fights back and knocks him off the top rope capitalizing it with his signature Dragon Driver to get the victory  

Dragon Lee wins via pinfall

Grayson Waller v Tyler Bate Singles match for the NXT World Championship

Bate starts off the match with laying Waller on his ass with numerous takedowns the champion is embarrassed by the challengers actions and uses his aggression to knock him down a notch or two  Waller continues to take control using the steel post and steps to his advantage and damaging his opponents torso The champion tries to capitalize the assault but his opponent is still resilient and fights back the challenger continues gaining momentum and delivers an airplane spin and a headbutt to take control The challenger recovers a bit more and attempts a dive but runs into a jumping Stunner against his opponent and retains the championship  

Grayson Waller retains via pinfall

After Waller celebrates his first title defense he begins to gloat in front of the commentary team but was confronted by Ijla Dragunov and before laying a hand on the champion he runs off and dismisses the former UK Champions challenge 

The following week Womens champion Tiffany Stratton defeats Thea Hail but is confronted by a returning Roxanne Perez and the challenge is set for the champion to defend her title against Perez sooner than later Briggs and Jensen finally collide with Henleys family bar on the line after a failed distraction from James and an assist from Henley the victor of the match is Josh Briggs Axiom interferes in one of The Schisms tag team matches and Gacy decides to lay the gauntlet wanting to decimate the masked highflyer to a match 

NXT

Gallus v Endris Enofe and Malik Blade

Enofe and Blade are looking for a title opportunity and believe that defeating the champions in a nontitle match will give them a shot Enofe brings the fight to Joe Coffey but Gallus keeps him isolated from his partner to prevent any threat to their championship Mark Coffey continues the assault against Enofe but after both competitors delivered a clothesline to each other and gave Enofe the opportunity to tag in Blade 

He enters the match with a ball of energy and tries to finish off the match but the champions refuse to suffer defeat and tries to deliver a top rope maneuver only for Wolfgang to distract him That distraction from Wolfgang gives Mark Coffey the advantage to knock him off the top rope and deliver his signature Crowning Glory for the victory  

After Gallus stands victorious approaching them was Chase University and brings the fight to them and Thea Hail strikes Wolfgang with a steel chair having them to retreat and vow that they will kick their asses 

Gallus wins via pinfall 

Axiom v Joe Gacy w The Schism

Soon as the bell rings The Schism surrounds the masked man around the ring and gives Gacy the advantage to dominate against him Axiom attempts to dodge his assaults and uses his agility to get over on his opponent But Gacy eventually gets the control back and targets his opponents torso until he began to fight back and deliver some momentum and deliver a top rope assault to Reid and Fowler  As he attempted to finish off Gacy Ava Raine rushes towards him and is struck with a running knee and that threw him off guard and gave Gacy the advantage to merciless beat him up and deliver a crossface to get the submission victory 

Joe Gacy wins via submission 

Tiffany Stratton v Roxanne Perez Twoout ofThree falls match for the NXT Womens Championship

In the first fall Stratton and Perez start off with some grappling but the challenger gets the upper hand and trying her best to get the first fall but the champion fights back with her own ways to get the first fall As Perez attempts her signature sunset flip powerbomb the champion counters it with an underhook pin and grabbing her tights to get the first fall 

Before the second fall could begin the champion assaults her challenger and lays her outside the ring trying to get the countout victory Before the referee could get to the count of nine Perez rushes back into the ring and that pisses off the champion and begins to find more ways to dominate against her opponent  She attempts a top rope moonsault but the challenger escapes and delivers a shining wizard to get the second fall victory 

Its the final fall both women give each other hell with Perez right arm being wounded and she tried to finish her opponent with a suplex but her arm gives out and that gives the champion the window to add more insult to injury and deliver a reverse STO to get the victory and retain her title  

Tiffany Stratton retains via pinfall 

After celebrating her victory Stratton adds some insult to injury and assaults Perez until officials break it up and that results in a backstage brawl between Waller and Dragunov with the champion getting the upper hand and using his sportscar as a weapon to add insult to injury The tournament continues with Dragon Lee and Fredericks being the fan favorites of it but they run into a roadblock with opponents in the semifinals Bronco Nima and Myles Borne 

After Lee and Fredericks are victorious in their respective bouts its announced that they are set to face each other in the tournament finals at NXT Great American Bash and the North American Champion Tony DAngelo will be watching the match by ringside After another title defense Katana Chance and Kayden Carter continue to look for a challenge and approaching them is the WWE Womens Tag Team Champions Iyo Sky and Dakota Kai of Damage CTRL They have the same problem looking for a challenge in their division and decided to challenge them in a title unification match 

NXT GREAT AMERICAN BASH 

Dragon Lee v Karl Fredericks NXT Mens Breakout Tournament Finals

The match starts with Fredericks uses his size against Lee but the luchador isnt going down easy and uses his speed and agility against his opponents strikes and technical abilities The Young Lion winner stops his opponents tracks and begins to lay numerous strikes to him and tries to deliver a top rope move but Lee catches him and nails him with a top rope armdrag giving him the advantage 

Lee continues to gain momentum but Fredericks continue to fight back but fails to gain momentum with his opponent delivering his signature Desnucadora to get the win  

Dragon Lee wins via pinfall

Gallus v Chase University Andre Chase and Duke Hudson w Thea Hail NXT Tag Team Championship

Duke Hudson starts off the match against Wolfgang the two lockup but Wolfgang wins the exchange and uses his heavyweight abilities to get the upper hand He eventually tags in Mark Coffey to gain some momentum for them and continues to dominate until a failed attack and that gave Hudson the window to tag in Chase 

He enters the match bringing the fight to the champions and has Hail to give him an assist but that led to the referee to eject her from ringside that gave Gallus the opportunity to handicap him while Hudson is upset with Hail getting involved in their match  Gallus continues the assault on Chase and that resulted in Hudson grabbing the towel from Hail and throwing it the ring to prevent any assault to Chase 

Gallus retains via technical knockout 

Kayden Carter and Katana Chance v Damage CTRL w Bayley for the NXT and WWE Womens Tag Team Championship in a title unification match

Starting off the match is Chance and Sky the two women attempt to use their agility against each other with Chance impressing Sky but the former NXT Womens Champion uses her veteran experience against her opponent 

Kai is tagged continuing to dominate Chance preventing her to tag in Carter but after a failed team maneuver Carter is tagged in the match and gains momentum for her team but failed to get the victory Sky and Kai begin to outnumber Carter but Chance enters to even the field but is taken out by Kai  As Kai tries to deliver a corner kick to her opponent but is countered by Carter and gives Chance the opportunity to deliver a  Splash to get the victory   

UNIFIED CHAMPIONSKayden Carter and Katana Chance wins via pinfall

Grayson Waller v Ijla Dragunov singles match for the NXT Championship

Waller dodges Dragunovs sick and twisted attacks but after awhile the former UK Champion gets his hands on the Aussie SOB and begins to disjoint his hand and arms But the champion usually exits the ring to prevent any defeat against Dragunov 

Dragunov goes for his signature uppercut but the champion dodges and lets his opponent hit an expose turnbuckle That gives the champion a window of opportunity and delivers an elbow drop to opponents head and gets the victory to retain the title 

Grayson Waller retains via pinfall Carnage Tour IV Night Three Booking NXT After WrestleMania
